    <div id="node-1086175" class="node node-teaser node-type-story"><div class="node-inner">



  

 <a href="/content/lock-free-multi-producer-multi-consumer-queue-ring-buffer" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"><img src="http://www.linuxjournal.com/files/linuxjournal.com/ufiles/imagecache/teaser/nodeimage/story/servers_0.jpg" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-teaser" width="100" height="100" /></a> 
  
  


      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/lock-free-multi-producer-multi-consumer-queue-ring-buffer" title="Lock-Free Multi-Producer Multi-Consumer Queue on Ring Buffer">Lock-Free Multi-Producer Multi-Consumer Queue on Ring Buffer</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/alexander-krizhanovsky" title="View user profile.">Alexander Krizh...</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Jun 12, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_19 first"><a href="/tag/how-tos" rel="tag" title="">HOW-TOs</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_241 active"><a href="/tag/hpc" rel="tag" title="" class="active">HPC</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_865 last"><a href="/tag/multicore" rel="tag" title="">multicore</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/lock-free-multi-producer-multi-consumer-queue-ring-buffer" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>
Nowadays, high-performance server software (for example, the HTTP accelerator) in most
cases
runs on multicore machines. Modern hardware could provide 32, 64 or more CPU
cores. In such highly concurrent environments, lock contention sometimes hurts
overall system performance more than data copying, context switches and so
on.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/lock-free-multi-producer-multi-consumer-queue-ring-buffer"> more>></a></span></p>
  </div>



  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_comments first last"><a href="/content/lock-free-multi-producer-multi-consumer-queue-ring-buffer#comments" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">24 comments</a></li>
</ul>
 <!---->




