 <a href="/content/april-2013-issue-linux-journal-high-performance-computing" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"><img src="http://www.linuxjournal.com/files/linuxjournal.com/ufiles/imagecache/teaser/nodeimage/story/cover228.jpg" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-teaser" width="100" height="100" /></a> 
  
  


      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/april-2013-issue-linux-journal-high-performance-computing" title="April 2013 Issue of Linux Journal: High Performance Computing">April 2013 Issue of Linux Journal: High Performance Computing</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/shawn-powers" title="View user profile.">Shawn Powers</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Apr 01, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_241 first active"><a href="/tag/hpc" rel="tag" title="" class="active">HPC</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_29 last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/29" rel="tag" title="">Linux Journal</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/april-2013-issue-linux-journal-high-performance-computing" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        


<p>
When I was in college, there was a rich kid down the hall who had a
computer with 16MB of RAM. Before you scoff, you need to think back to
1993.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/april-2013-issue-linux-journal-high-performance-computing"> more>></a></span></p>
